caption: A quaint drink and food spot in Old Town with a solid menu and decently priced food. I was told that all the food is made fresh to order. They have specialty/seasonal cocktails. The back patio seating is where you want to be on a nice day. The wait staff was attentive and quick.

Have eaten lunch here three times on visits to Chicago and have never failed to get a very tasty meal that was prepared and delivered quickly enough to enjoy my lunch hour. If you are in the vicinity, I heartily recommend lunching here.

This restaurant/bar is surprising with their diverse and interesting menu. Everything tastes very fresh and is well put together. Even the traditional bar fare has a spin on it. Service is great and they have large outdoor space. a welcome place in the neighborhood.

This place is awesome for lunch. Come to the city few times a week and always look For a local spot that offers good selection of drinks and affordable lunch menu. This time we found ourselves in old town. Decided to try Wells on Wells. The lunch menu had many items on it for $8.50 which included fries, waffle fries or chips. We got a pub burger with waffle fries and a turkey wrap with regular fries. Both items were big enough to share and equally delicious. Place has a full service bar with a great selection of beers and mixed drinks. This is definitely a good place for a great lunch or after work drink.

Terrible Experience. I used to work in the food industry for a long time. Everyone knows the #1 rule "CUSTOMER IS ALWAYS RIGHT". I get it, it sucks when they are actually wrong, but what I learned being in the industry is that if you want a good tip, you do whatever to make the customer happy even if they are being a pain.  I was there during Cubs Game 6. My friend and I ordered the grilled cheese and we were under the impression it came with soup plus a side. we realized we were wrong when we got our meal with no soup since we both ordered sides. IN MY OPINION, the menu was misleading and when i am expecting a side and don't get it, obviously I am going to bring it up. We told out waitress, we both said we will pay for the extra side, just please get it for us. Instead of just taking our order and fixing it, she gave us attitude and looked at us as if we were speaking another language and proceeded to tell her manager. The manager came over and was trying to explain how we were wrong and they have had the same menu for 12 years and made us feel stupid for thinking it came with two sides. I told her I didn't care, just to please get us our side of soup. and that we will actually pay for it. She then was trying to change our mind on ordering it since their kitchen was backed up. I don't know why no one there understood our request. We just wanted soup.  If it was me, I would have said "I am so sorry for the confusion. I will get that order in ASAP" and i would personally go to the kitchen and try to get the soup myself. Instead we waited 45 min to get it. It's soup, takes 5 min. I would have cut other orders to fix the current problem.  So naturally I tipped extremely low and I hear the waitress bitching at another waiter about it. Sorry, but if you want a good tip, you provide good, attitude-less, service.  I will never go here again.

This spot and Corcorans are pretty much the two bars to go to after your sporting event on North Ave beach (volleyball) or Lincoln Park turf fields (soccer). They both have sidewalk cafe tables and back patios, offer happy hour specials, and group specials for your team. Last time I went, our team got the Pacifico buckets and appetizers for about $20/person. I got the beet salad and unfortunately, there were barely any beets- only a few chopped pretty small, sprinkled on a large salad. Our server forgot one of our fish tacos and put it on the house, so I'd say they take care of you despite the crowding and overall roudy-ness.

I'm usually a fan of standard bar food. So when I hear there's a place with really good bar food my expectations are a decent burger and some good appetizers.  Wells on Wells will far exceed that expectation. We went there early a few weeks back to we could get a seat in the patio area that filled up pretty quickly.  Everyone there was friendly and while the wings were just OK the chorizo stuffed potato skins were amazing (who doesn't love chorizo?) and pretzel bites were a must order (awesome sauce with them too which perfectly compliment them.)  For dinner I had the blackened chicken Caesar and it had just the right kick to make it stand out.  The refills came quick even when they were packed and for those on a budget there were a variety of drink specials that varied daily as well as some food specials throughout the beginning of the week.  Good atmosphere, good food, good time!
